data.body:
Resources on the edge of maps cause game to crash on loading.

Reproduced by creating a map with the following map parameters:
Size (32,32)
Cordon Left/Top (0,0)
Cordon Right/Bottom(32,32)
Place ore in the top left corner, save the map and the map will fail on loading with an index out of bounds exception. The dimensions of the map don't matter, you just need to place Ore on the edge cells of the map. 

The code below throws the exception and from what I can tell it tries to find the surrounding cells of the ore but because its on the edge cell of a map it goes out of bounds.

ResourceLayer.cs

``` csharp
        int GetAdjacentCellsWith(ResourceType t, int i, int j)
        {
            var sum = 0;
            for (var u = -1; u < 2; u++)
                for (var v = -1; v < 2; v++)
                    if (content[i + u, j + v].Type == t)
                        ++sum;
            return sum;
        }
```

I ran some further tests and if you let resources grow towards the edge of the map once the resource is "fully matured" on the edge cell of the map it will attempt to grow outwards and crash the game as well.
